<div>
    <ul>
        <li><img src="/icons/wifi-4bars.svg" />An icon representing the strength of the robot wifi signal</li>
        <li><img src="/icons/battery.png" />An icon depicting the state of the robot battery</li>
        <li><img src="/icons/eye-found.svg" />An icon reflecting the status of robot detection</li>
        <li><img src="/icons/compass.png" />The current location and orientation of the robot</li>
        <li><img src="/icons/stop.png" />An Emergency Stop button</li>
    </ul>
    <div><b>Clicking the emergency stop button will stop the robot, turn off all cutters and Pause the current excursion.</b><br/><br/>
    Hovering over the wifi icon will display additional information:
    <ul>
        <li>The connection status and hotspot connected to</li>
        <li>The Received Signal Strength (RSSI) and signal quality</li>
        <li>The last time telemetry was updated</li>
        <li>The robot uptime</li>
    </ul>     
    Hovering over the battery icon will display further sensor details, typically:
    <ul>
        <li>The battery level sampled at standstill</li>
        <li>The battery level sampled in motion</li>
    </ul>     
    Hovering over the robot detection icon will display:
    <ul>
        <li>The locate time and frame rate</li>
        <li>The confidence level of current projection</li>
        <li>Quality statistics from the detection system</li>
    </ul>
    You can click these icons to toggle a more permanent pop-up information bubble. 
    </div> 
